IMPORTANT NOTICE REGARDING CLINICAL USE:

Open DQA is a data quality assessment tool intended to support—not replace—
human clinical judgment and institutional data governance processes. The
software identifies potential data quality issues based on rule-based heuristics
and statistical methods; all findings must be reviewed and validated by qualified
personnel before any clinical, administrative, or regulatory decisions are made.

The authors and contributors make no warranties regarding the clinical accuracy,
completeness, or fitness-for-purpose of quality check results. Use in production
clinical environments is the sole responsibility of the deploying institution.

Patient data processed by Open DQA remains entirely within the deploying
institution's infrastructure. No patient data is transmitted externally, except
where AI-powered features are explicitly enabled and configured, in which case
anonymized statistical summaries only are transmitted to third-party APIs.
